The paper deals with few-shot learning in image recognition, which is a problem commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method involves predicting parameters from activations in a neural network, which is a technique that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on image datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) research.
